OL,6,FCharges state that between June 3 and
OL,7,FJuly 20 in 2019, Hopper dishonestly
OL,8,Fmade a false representation to
OL,9,Finsurers Aviva and Old Mutual Health,
OL,10,Fthat his "legs had been amputated
OL,11,Fbecause of illness rather than self-
OL,12,Finflicted injury".
OL,14,FThe court heard Hopper had an
OL,15,F'obsession' and a 'sexual interest' in
OL,16,Famputation and body removal.
OL,18,FHopper told insurers he had
OL,19,F'septicaemia'
