OL,3,CSurgeon admits fraud after having his
OL,4,Cown legs removed
OL,6,FHe submerged his feet in dry ice for
OL,7,Feight hours, to the point they became
OL,8,F'unviable' and had to be removed in
OL,9,Fhospital.
OL,11,FHe was then admitted to the Royal
OL,12,FCornwall Hospital with suspected
OL,13,Fsepsis, and transferred to Derriford
OL,14,FHospital in Plymouth where he spent
OL,15,Fseveral weeks in a hyperbaric chamber,
OL,16,Fand his legs were later amputated
OL,17,Fbelow the knee.
