OL,6,FAndrew Langdon KC, mitigating, said
OL,7,Fhis client had grown up in a rural
OL,8,Fvillage in Wales and felt he was "in
OL,9,Fthe wrong body" from a young age.
OL,11,F"He was troubled by his gender, he
OL,12,Fwanted to be female," Mr Langdon said.
OL,14,FMr Langdon told how Hopper identified
OL,15,Fwith body integrity identity disorder
OL,16,Fand those with a desire to amputate
OL,17,Fone or more healthy limbs.
OL,19,FHopper described his thoughts about
OL,20,Fhis feet being amputated as
OL,21,F"persistent, never ending".
